segments.en:
The poem says:
Why does fleeting life so painfully rush about?
Even the grandest feast must end and break apart.
A thousand griefs and joys are equally airy dreams;
Past and present—one mad dream, all absurd.
Do not speak only of “red sleeves” and heavy tear-marks;
Still more are love-mad hearts that clasp long resentment.
Read every word: it is all blood;
Ten years of bitter toil are not a common thing.
